value.value: A benzonaphthyridine derivative, with antimalarial and potential antiviral activities. Upon administration, pyronaridine inhibits the formation of beta-hematin, which results in the accumulation of toxic heme within the parasite. In addition, pyronaridine inhibits glutathione-dependent degradation of hematin. This promotes hematin-induced lysis of red blood cells (RBCs), resulting in parasite death. Pyronaridine also exhibits antiviral activity against some viruses in vitro, including Ebola (EBOV) and severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV-2) viruses.

label.value: Stage III Testicular Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage III includes: Any pT/TX, Any N, M1, SX.  M1: Distant metastasis. SX: Marker studies not available or not performed.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
An amphiphilic piperidine agent shown to reduce plaque formation in vitro and to reduce gingivitis in vivo in an animal model.

A water-soluble prodrug of a pyridyl cyanoguanidine compound and an inhibitor of nicotinamide phosphoribosyltransferase (NAMPT) with potential antineoplastic activity. Teglarinad is rapidly converted in the bloodstream into an active compound through hydrolytic cleavage of the carbonate ester bond. The activated form inhibits NAMPT, thereby inhibiting nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD+) biosynthesis and induces a rapid decline in intracellular NAD+ followed by ATP reduction. As NAD+ is essential for tumor cell growth, inhibition of NAMPT induces tumor cell death. NAMPT is an essential enzyme in the synthesis of NAD+ and is upregulated in some cancers.

label.value: Stage IV Prostate Cancer AJCC v6

value.value: Stage IV includes: (T4, N0, M0); (Any T, N1, M0); (Any T, Any N, M1) (Any G).  T4: Tumor is fixed or invades adjacent structures other than seminal vesicles: bladder neck, external sphincter, rectum, levator muscles, and/or pelvic wall.  N1: Metastasis in regional lymph node(s).  M1: Distant metastasis.  (AJCC 6th ed.)
A diffuse large cell lymphoma occurring in children.
A thiosemicarbazone antimycobacterial agent with activity against isoniazid-resistant strains of Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

label.value: Refractory Malignant Testicular Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: Malignant testicular germ cell tumor that is resistant to treatment.
A derivative of isoniazid with antitubercular activity.
A semisynthetic derivative of rifamycin with a longer biological half-life than rifampicin.

A broad spectrum antibiotic used as a second-line antitubercular drug, effective against pulmonary and extrapulmonary tuberculosis. Terizidone has activity against Mycobacterium strains that are resistant to first-line drugs.
